HEADWORD: Remblai
<hw>Rem`blai"</hw> <pr>(r?n`bl?")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
remblayer to fill up an excavation, to embank.]</ety> <fld>(Fort. &
Engin.)</fld> <def>Earth or materials made into a bank after having been
excavated.</def>⟦br⟧
